<dl id="n01083i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n01" href="#n01083i">N01 (VI.B.10)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n01all.htm#n01083i"> 83(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ yog (fire)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[GIPSIES IN WINTER.]</font> It is part of his racial pride that makes the Romanichal reluctant to abandon the tawny tent in winter for a house. I have heard an old gipsy say that when lying convalescent in a hospital he &ldquo;was terribly afeared that the ceiling might come down on him.&rdquo; He was glad to get back to &ldquo;the old <i>tan</i>&rdquo; (tent) and put <i>kosht</i> (wood) on the <mark><i>yog</i> (fire)</mark> and &ldquo;feel comfortable-like again.&rdquo; <small> <a name="DM28dec22" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#DM28dec22"><cite title="source">Daily Mail</cite></a> (28 December 1922) 6/5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c05145k" href="c05all.htm#c05145k">VI.C.05:145(k)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
